[normal]4. 
[normal]Science and discovery centres such as At-Bristol are ideal venues for bringing science research and the public together, for investigation 
[normal]and dialogue.
[normal]              
[normal]Over the last 2 years, At-Bristol has undertaken a significant programme of energy reduction and sustainability activity. We have won multiple awards, from food procurement standards, to carbon and energy reduction. 
[normal]Achievements include:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]We use the technology and systems of the science centre building (e.g. 50 kW peak 
[normal]Photovoltaic
[normal] array, green roof, eutectic tank heat exchange system
[normal], advanced energy monitori
[normal]ng
[normal]) to bring the science of sustainability to life, to act as a ‘living case study’ and provide positive and engaging examples of success. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]By leading the way as an exemplar centre of positive change for energy reduction, we provide an exciting and truste
[normal]d informal learning environment, and a fantastic springboard for climate science discussion and debate.
[normal]&#xa0;
